===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|网|非|ls=ic|alt1=罒|t1=net|t2=mistake}}. The original version is [[𦋛]] and its original meaning was a net for fishing, then used instead of [[辠]] due to the similarity of the latter character to [[皇]], which represents the Emperor.

===Etymology===
Unclear. Possibly of {{der|zh|sit}} origin and cognate with {{cog|lus|sual||{{n-g|(adj.)}} bad, evil, vile, corrupt; {{n-g|(v. tr.)}} (to attempt) to criminally assault, to rape (a woman)}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

